The number of coronavirus cases in South Africa has risen to 592 144 after 2 258 new cases were confirmed in the past 24 hours. The Department of Health says 282 additional COVID-19 related deaths were recorded on Tuesday, bringing the total death toll in the country to 12 264. The total number of recoveries is 485 468, translating to a total recovery rate of 82%. “66 deaths from the Eastern Cape, 89 from Gauteng, 57 from KwaZulu-Natal, 3 from Northern Cape, 13 from the Free State, 34 from the Western Cape and 20 from the North West,” reads a statement from the Health Department. The Western Cape still has the highest number of fatalities in the country with 3 646 followed by Gauteng and the Eastern Cape with 3 018 and 2 633 respectively. 3 430 347 592 144 485 468 94 412 12 264 497 732 As at  18 August 2020 14 677 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document)); 